        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14067",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "to 1) Why should a user use PHP's functions.... Zend_Date has all a user needs. \nto 2) Zend_Date is consistent... the API is feature rich, simple to use and has no known problems.\nto 3) Zend_Date has more than 100 functions... I dont think that \"more\" is necessary\nto 4) it's PHP's fault not to support 64bit timestamps ;-)\n\nI will not give access to the internal mktime or getdate function to prevent the illusion that they are 100% identical to the php functions.\n\nBut I see the possible benefit to have Zend_Date extracted as array and have an array as input.\nFirst is already implemented with getDateParts() and will become public.\nFor the details on the second I have to think about.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-04-08T17:10:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-04-08T17:10:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14068",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "1) Agreed, but it would be nice if the developer had easier access (no need to create subclasses) :)\n2) Zend_Date API is missing public methods equivalent to PHP's {{mkdate()}} and {{getdate()}}.\n3) 100 functions, but see 2) above.\n4) Agreed!\n\n{quote}I will not give access to the internal mktime or getdate function to prevent the illusion that they are 100% identical to the php functions.{quote}\n\nYes, there are many ways to provide 2) above that do not require exposing internal functions.\nIt would be convenient if Zend_Date had a method similar to {{getdate()}} and the output of this method could be used as input to Zend_Date's method for creating date objects from these parts.\n\n{code}\n$dateParts = Zend_Date::now()->getArrayOfDateParts();\n$dateObject = Zend_Date::mkDateObject($dateParts);\n{code}\n\nI chose silly long method names to avoid confusion with any existing methods.  The public methods could be all new, or some type of proxy to internal methods, or by making an internal method public.  I am only trying to suggest the usefulness of allowing the output of one function to be used as the input for the other function (making date objects).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-04-08T17:42:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-04-08T17:42:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14620",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "We will include this feature after the release of 1.0.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-15T15:15:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-15T15:15:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15709",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Added the new function toArray() which returns an array representation of the actual date object.\nEqual to PHP's getDate() function.\n\nIntegrated with SVN 5613\n\nCreation of dates from an array will come in the future.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-07-07T12:24:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-07-07T12:24:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15711",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Added the possibility to use arrays as input values for all methods which accept date input values.\n\nIncluded with SVN-5618",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
